modules.description: This module provides functions to interact with an InfluxDB server, specifically supporting ping and write operations. It works with InfluxDB hosts, databases, and time series data points, using asynchronous deferred responses for handling I/O. Concrete use cases include sending a health check to an InfluxDB instance and writing batches of data points to a specified database.

This module implements a client for interacting with InfluxDB, supporting asynchronous ping and write operations. It handles communication with InfluxDB hosts and manages time series data points for writing to specific databases. It is used to send health checks and batch time series data to InfluxDB instances.
